      "readme_summary": "<p align=\"center\"> <img src=\"assets/colibri.svg\" width=\"500\" alt=\"colibrì — tiny engine, immense model\"> </p> **Tiny engine, immense model.** Run **GLM-5.2 (744B-parameter MoE)** on a consumer machine with ~25 GB of RAM — in pure C, with zero dependencies, by streaming experts from disk. Colibrì is a lightweight, quality-preserving MoE runtime that treats VRAM, RAM, and storage as one managed memory hierarchy. Insufficient fast memory may reduce speed, but the default policy never silently changes model precision or router semantics. ``` $ ./coli chat 🐦 colibrì v1.0 — GLM-5.2 · 744B MoE · int4 · streaming CPU ✓ ready in 32s · resident 9.9 GB › ciao! ◆ Ciao! 😊 Come posso aiutarti oggi? ``` #…",
